{
  "stem": "4963.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I remember my other grandmother quite well because I would stop by there and get some-- get some cake and so on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I was named after my grandfather, my mother's father, Mathis.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So my Hebrew name was really [INAUDIBLE], something like it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But they called me Marcia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We didn't have any middle names in those days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "My mother also had a brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He was a doctor-- [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Labat ?] Taft.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then he had another-- she had another brother, Gershon Taft.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He was in charge of the bakery when my grandfather died.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And two of my aunts on my father's side lived in Kovno.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "One-- one-- one sister's name was Paula, and she was quite significant in my life.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, later on I will tell you that when-- she really-- I lived with them, with my Aunt Paula and Aunt Chassia.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Aunt Chassia passed away in Stutthof.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, my-- on my father's side-- and then I had another aunt who was in Paris.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she was Assia.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her name was Assia.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I did, when I came to the United States, I lived with her, and she really was the one who brought me out here.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she was really like a second mother to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now my-- my father, as I mentioned-- my mother, as I mentioned, had two brothers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, well, what else can I tell you?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were, as I said, we-- we were very well off.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so we had-- What was your school experience like?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I went to Hebrew school and [INAUDIBLE] Gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First I went to [INAUDIBLE], I think, for a year, and then [INAUDIBLE] Gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And until 1940.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In 1940, the Russians came to Lithuania, and we were forbidden to go to Hebrew schools.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
